@startuml
title LMS Use Case Diagram 
left to right direction
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false

actor Student
actor Instructor
actor "Auth Service" as Auth
actor "Email Service" as Email

rectangle "Learning Management System" {

  usecase "Sign In" as UC1
  usecase "Enroll in Course" as UC2
  usecase "View Course Content" as UC3
  usecase "Submit Assignment" as UC4
  usecase "Grade Assignment" as UC5
  usecase "Send Notification" as UC6
}

Student --> UC1
Student --> UC2
Student --> UC3
Student --> UC4

Instructor --> UC1
Instructor --> UC3
Instructor --> UC5
Instructor --> UC6

Auth --> UC1
Email --> UC6

UC2 ..> UC1 : <<include>>
UC4 ..> UC1 : <<include>>
UC5 ..> UC1 : <<include>>
UC6 ..> UC4 : <<extend>>

note right of Student
Primary user who logs in, enrolls in courses,
views content, and submits assignments.
end note

note right of Instructor
Primary user who manages learning activities
by grading assignments and sending updates.
end note

note right of Auth
Secondary external system that authenticates
users and returns success/failure to the LMS.
end note

note right of Email
Secondary external system used by the LMS to
send emails such as confirmations and announcements.
end note

note right of UC1
User signs in and the LMS verifies identity using
the authentication service before allowing access.
end note

note right of UC2
Student enrolls in a course so the LMS can grant
access to materials and course activities.
end note

note right of UC3
Student or Instructor views course resources such as
lectures, files, announcements, and syllabus content.
end note

note right of UC4
Student submits an assignment and the LMS stores the
submission with a timestamp for instructor review.
end note

note right of UC5
Instructor reviews a submission and records a grade
and feedback so students can see results.
end note

note right of UC6
LMS sends email notifications, for example after a
successful submission or when an instructor announces updates.
end note

@enduml
